result.name: Kim's garden

reviews.text: Taste ok but a bit pricy. And too hot inside while eating spicy food.

Really nice restaurant there! The owner also kind and nice to the guest. The place looks like also a plce for korean's who live in hongkong to eat or just having a little drink there. For the food, its my first time tasting the real korean food outside my origin country, so for me its quite good for the taste. #hongkong #koreanfood #kowloon
cozy place. they serve set foods, i like their soft tofu soup, price is ok also.

My wife and I stumbled upon this small Korean restaurant in Kowloon City. They do not have barbeque. They serve various cooked dishes, soups, noodles and rice. My wife ordered the spicy beef soup (yukaejang) set and I had the spicy soft tofu seafood soup (sundubu-jjigae) set. 

We were pleasantly surprised that the food tasted quite authentic. I was even contemplating bringing my mom to try the ginseng chicken soup. All the goodwill went down the drain when my wife got sick soon after the meal. The kimchi and/or the other side dishes that she ate, were probably contaminated.
Great food with the best service, i love the owners this is by far my favorite restaurant in all of Hong Kong!  When i was studying abroad i would come here almost everyday
